        "client_msg_id": "384c249d-0416-4ccd-b110-f4d1b8618cfa",
        "text": "Finally had time today to write some DAML! :slightly_smiling_face:\n\nHappy to take feedback: <https:\/\/github.com\/DLC-link\/canton\/pull\/4\/files>\n\n• I realized, compared to the drawings made earlier, that putting Request-State updating choices on the Requests itself makes more sense, but currently its a mix. Creation happens through the Account contract, state updates on self. Not sure what the cleanest\/recommended way would be. Making a Rules factory for the Request template as well? Or this is fine?\n• I also wonder if the 'id' field solution made to replace our ~UUIDs is necessary for the Requests. I wonder how other projects solve the problem of tracking a contract instance's life-cycle without it. Say we want to show the user's ongoing requests on a UI. I understand we query for all they are privy to; but is there a way to keep _knowing_ that a UI object referencing a contract instance is the updated version of a previous object, without local state and this uuid hack?\nThanks for taking a look! :pray:\n\n<@UEHLS0JUB> <@UMW95BAT1> <@U9V802QQ6> <@U05FU0HPZ9T>",
