        "client_msg_id": "ec1b95b5-c780-48a2-84ca-e723da941468",
        "text": "Great answers and follow-up questions. Thanks to you both. \n\nFor our other products, the UI lets our users build and submit Bitcoin transactions as well as interact with the minted ibtc token, specifically burn it from the wallet.\n\nI guess my first thought is that we could use our externally hosted web app to manage the Bitcoin actions and it would be better to use the Canton hosted app for the ibtc actions such as burn.\n\nHowever, it might make more sense to just put all that functionality into the same app. That's probably going to be a much simpler experience for the user. So that single app would be on the validator. \n\nIs that tracking with what you guys are thinking? I'll sync up with Robert today as well to discuss further. Thanks for your help",
